Project Chat Navigation Fix Log
================================
Test Time: 2025-06-17 13:50
Purpose: Fix chat details not showing when opening from project view

Issue:
- When clicking on a chat in the project detail view, the chat page opened but didn't show the chat details
- Chat appeared empty despite navigation working

Root Cause:
- Project detail was passing wrong URL parameter
- Was using: /chat?session=${session.id}
- Chat page expects: /chat?thread=${threadId}

Fix Applied:
In project-detail.tsx handleContinueChat function:
- Changed from: router.push(`/chat?session=${session.id}`)
- Changed to: router.push(`/chat?thread=${session.thread_id}`)

How it works:
1. Project detail view has the session object with thread_id
2. Chat page's main.tsx reads the 'thread' parameter from URL
3. If thread parameter exists, it calls loadChat(threadId)
4. loadChat fetches the session by thread ID and loads all messages

Current Status:
- Frontend changes applied (no restart needed for Next.js dev server)
- Chat navigation should now work properly
- Clicking on a chat in project view will load the full chat history

Test: Click on a chat from the project detail view to verify it loads the messages.